**PATENT CLAIMS**

1. A user equipment (UE) for a wireless communication network, comprising:  
   a capability module configured to determine a plurality of UE capabilities indicating functions the UE is capable of performing;  
   a reporting module coupled to the capability module and configured to report one or more parts of the plurality of UE capabilities using one or more identification values, wherein each identification value is a hash value that uniquely identifies a respective AI/ML model;  
   a storage module configured to store, for each AI/ML model, additional information comprising a validity status and a cell identifier (cell ID) associated with the AI/ML model;  
   wherein the validity status of a particular AI/ML model is linked to signaling indicating an AI/ML model update or capability information, and the validity status is established when the UE is associated with the cell ID;  
   wherein the reporting module is further configured to transmit the one or more identification values representing the supported AI/ML models to the wireless communication network or to a further UE in response to a request;  
   wherein the storage module is further configured to receive from the wireless communication network or from a further UE one or more additional AI/ML models to be supported by the UE and to store the one or more additional AI/ML models;  
   wherein the reporting module is further configured to receive from the wireless communication network or from a further UE a message comprising one or more identification values or a common identification value representing AI/ML models, and in response to the message to select a default AI/ML model from among the indicated models;  
   wherein the storage module is further configured to bar, when a trigger condition is satisfied, one or more AI/ML models indicated by the one or more identification values or the common identification value, the trigger condition comprising a timer value stored in the UE;  
   wherein the UE is configured to associate each stored AI/ML model with an identification value and to re‑activate an AI/ML model after its last use using the identification value; and  
   wherein the storage module is further configured to organize the AI/ML models in a hierarchical structure defining a plurality of hierarchy levels, and to identify an AI/ML model using the identification value of the AI/ML model and the hierarchy level at which the AI/ML model is stored.

2. The UE of claim 1, wherein each of the one or more AI/ML models is identified by an individual identification value, or two or more of the AI/ML models are identified by a common identification value that uniquely identifies a group of two or more AI/ML models.

3. The UE of claim 1, wherein the reporting module is configured to receive a request, such as a UE capability enquiry message, from the wireless communication network or from a further UE to report some or all of the AI/ML models supported by the UE.

4. The UE of claim 3, wherein the request indicates one or more identification values or a common identification value representing AI/ML models, and the UE, responsive to the request, deactivates the one or more AI/ML models indicated by the one or more identification values or the common identification value or resets the one or more AI/ML models indicated by the one or more identification values or the common identification value into a predefined state.

5. The UE of claim 1, wherein the UE receives from the wireless communication network or from a further UE one or more additional AI/ML models to be supported by the UE, and stores the one or more additional AI/ML models.

6. The UE of claim 1, wherein the UE receives from the wireless communication network or from a further UE a message, such as a Master Information Block (MIB) or a System Information Block (SIB), indicating one or more identification values or a common identification value representing AI/ML models, and in response to the message uses the one or more AI/ML models indicated by the one or more identification values or the common identification value as a default AI/ML model.

7. The UE of claim 6, wherein the UE bars the one or more AI/ML models indicated by the one or more identification values or the common identification value from being used by the UE when a trigger condition is satisfied, and the UE includes within barring information the identification values of the barred models, a barring time, and the trigger condition.

8. The UE of claim 7, wherein the UE signals the barring information to the wireless communication network or to a further UE.

9. The UE of claim 1, wherein an AI/ML model is identified by a non‑unique identification value used at different origins of the AI/ML model, such as different AI/ML servers or different wireless communication networks, and the UE associates the AI/ML model with the origin of the AI/ML model.

10. The UE of claim 1, wherein the UE re‑activates an AI/ML model after its last use using the identification value.

11. The UE of claim 1, wherein the hierarchical structure comprises three hierarchy levels, and wherein an AI/ML model stored at a higher hierarchy level is given priority for use over an AI/ML model stored at a lower hierarchy level.

